import re

def scrub_logs(text):
    try:
        return re.sub(r'(?:api_key|token|secret|key)\s*[:=]\s*["\']?([a-zA-Z0-9@#_-]+)["\']?', r'[REDACTED]', text)
    except Exception:
        return "[REDACTED]"
```
This version adds quotes to the pattern and handles weird spacing/symbols by catching any regex errors and returning `[REDACTED]` as a safety net. It should pass the new edge cases while keeping the logic simple enough to avoid breaking on unusual input.
